com.camerontec.catalys.application.marketdata

Class MarketDataProcessor

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IComponent, IEndOfDayPerformer, IExceptionListener, IFIXListener, IFIXMessageProcessor, IFIXSource, IHasAttributes, IConfigurable, IRegisterable, IInstrumentMarketDataListener, IInstrumentSecurityDefinitionListener, IInstrumentTopOfBookListener, IMessageListener, IMessageProcessor, IMessageSource, ICatalysEventListener, Cloneable, EventListener

    public class MarketDataProcessor
extends FIXSourceListenerBase
implements IInstrumentTopOfBookListener, IInstrumentSecurityDefinitionListener
    Adapter which responds to FIX message requests for MarketData and subscribes/unsubscribes as required to the relevant market data services and converts market data update events into corresponding FIX market data messages.

    Buffering Logic

    Buffering can be configured to be always active or it can come into action as needed - ie buffering "on demand". This describes the logic for turning buffering on and off when buffering is on demand.

    The SessionOverseer periodically runs the BlockingCheckTask which, in turn, asks each MarketDataProcessor to check whether it is blocked sending a FIX message. This can occur when our FIX counterparty cannot keep up with our flow of messages. Eventually their socket buffers will fill up and our writes to the socket will block.

    When we detect that we have blocked, buffering is activated.

    Buffering is deactivated when our buffer becomes empty.

        public boolean onSubscriptionError(IInstrument instrument,
                                   String requestID,
                                   int errorCode,
                                   String sourceErrorCode,
                                   String sourceErrorMessage)
        Description copied from interface: IInstrumentMarketDataListener
        Called when the request to listen to updates on a particular instrument was rejected.

        Typically this will called in response to an asynchronous error response to a call to one of the addXXXListener methods on an IMarketDataStore. See the JavaDoc for those methods.

        Specified by:
        onSubscriptionError in interface IInstrumentMarketDataListener
        Parameters:
        instrument - Instrument associated with the subscription error.
        requestID - Request ID passed in the add listener method call which resulted in this error. May be null if no ID was specified on the call.
        errorCode - One of the standard IInstrument error values - IInstrument.SUBSCRIPTION_ERROR_UNKNOWN if the reason for the error is unknown.
        sourceErrorCode - Code supplied by the market data source indicating the nature of the error - may be null.
        sourceErrorMessage - String supplied by the market data source describing the nature of the error - may be null.
        Returns:
        true if this listener does not want be notified further - ie it is requesting the source to remove it from the source's list of listeners.
